children.name: Fonts (use for Styles; not exported as tokens)

Fonts are combined from several properties: Font Sizes, Font Weights, Line Heights etc. Any typographic elements—in Figma as well as any heading elements meant to be exported through the Elements page—should be composed in Fonts, and then used in those use-cases. As long as they use values derived from (“conform to”) the other tokenized frames (again, Line Heights, Font Weights etc.) then those will work well just as well in code as inside of Figma.
